ZH: 分裂是一种常见的社会现象。
EN: Division is a common social phenomenon.

ZH: 这个国家正面临着分裂的危险。
EN: This country is facing the danger of division.

ZH: 分裂会带来不稳定和冲突。
EN: Division can bring instability and conflict.

ZH: 政治分裂可能导致国家分崩离析。
EN: Political division can lead to the disintegration of a country.

ZH: 家庭内的分裂可能导致破裂。
EN: Division within a family can lead to a break-up.

ZH: 这两个组织之间存在着分裂。
EN: There is a division between these two organizations.

ZH: 宗教分裂导致了内战。
EN: Religious division led to a civil war.

ZH: 分裂思想造成了人们之间的对立。
EN: Divisive thinking has caused opposition among people.

ZH: 他们之间的分裂造成了团队的失败。
EN: The division between them led to the failure of the team.

ZH: 这场选举导致了一场分裂的政治危机。
EN: The election led to a divisive political crisis.

ZH: 分裂在社会中造成了裂痕。
EN: Division has caused cracks in society.

ZH: 这种分裂趋势不可持续。
EN: This divisive trend is not sustainable.

ZH: 他试图消除分裂并促进和解。
EN: He is trying to eliminate division and promote reconciliation.

ZH: 他对这种分裂感到沮丧。
EN: He is frustrated by this division.

ZH: 我们必须努力避免任何形式的分裂。
EN: We must work hard to avoid any form of division.

ZH: 分裂只会带来痛苦和破坏。
EN: Division only brings pain and destruction.

ZH: 社会分裂会导致混乱和不和谐。
EN: Social division can lead to chaos and disharmony.

ZH: 通过团结一致，我们可以避免分裂。
EN: By standing united, we can avoid division.

ZH: 唯有消除分裂，才能实现和平与进步。
EN: Only by eliminating division can we achieve peace and progress.

ZH: 只有团结一心，我们才能战胜分裂。
EN: Only by standing united can we overcome division.
